law.text:
In addition to other activities not prohibited, any statistical agent is authorized, on behalf of its members and subscribers, to:
Develop statistical plans including territorial and class definitions;
Collect historical data from members, subscribers, or any other source;
Distribute information that is required or directed to be filed with the commissioner;
Collect, compile, and distribute past and current prices of individual insurers and publish such information;
Collect and compile exposure and loss experience for the purpose of individual risk experience ratings; and
Furnish any other services, as approved or directed by the commissioner, related to those enumerated in this section.
